				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I actually when I first started EQ (having not read the manual, or anything) kinda thought this was how everything was going to work anyway.
<br />

<br />
Where you started off with like a generic mage, and then you put your points into things YOU wanted, so, you could be a nuker mage with a pet side kick, or a pet master with an itch for a nuke. I stupidly thought that nukes would get more powerful as you were better in the skill so your lvl 1 nuke would do 1 to start with and say end at 5 when you were about to get the next level.
<br />

<br />
As a result, I kinda like the generic pet you put points in to suit YOUR playstyle thing.  While most of us will raid at some point, I generally solo, so, I kinda need a seriously beefy pet, coz its me and him.  A group pet could be more cunning, maybe need points in more tactics such as pet to get intellegence to try and be behind the mob, a raid pet would need maybe anti push, that kind of thing.
<br />

<br />
I think it would be nice if there were more options to develop your pet to be a more unique thing rather than everyones earth pet being the same.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
